      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KENNYS SON (6) finished second at Melton two starts back then did a great job again at his latest appearance over 2150m at at Bendigo, beaten 8 metres into third after being handy all the way. Tackles a similar assignment and he can take care of this line-up. LITTLE MISS MORGAN (5) scored by 4 metres at Bendigo over 2150m last start at her first run back from a spell. That latest effort is good enough to put her right in the finish. THE ITALIAN DREAM (3) was unplaced two starts ago then things went wrong last start when she broke and finished 30 metres away in tenth over 2150m at Bendigo. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Only needs to get things right to be in the money. ALDEBARAN MARCUS (2) is the best of the rest after finishing third over 2230m at Globe Derby Park last time out. Include from the low draw.",
